# File 4: README.md (Root of your project)

# World Conflict & Development Heat Map

An interactive visualization showing the correlation between geographic distance from conflict zones and development indices.

## 🌍 Features

- Interactive world map with conflict and development zones
- Real-time data visualization with HDI scores
- Mobile-responsive design
- Touch-friendly interactions
- Animated heat map effects

## 🚀 Live Demo

Visit: [Your Vercel URL will be here]

## 📱 Mobile Optimized

- Works on all devices (phones, tablets, desktop)
- Touch gestures and interactions
- Responsive layout that adapts to screen size
- Landscape and portrait mode support

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Pure HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
- SVG for crisp vector graphics
- CSS animations and transitions
- Responsive design with media queries

## 📊 Data Sources

The visualization is based on:

- Global Peace Index data
- Human Development Index (HDI)
- Historical conflict analysis
- Geographic correlation studies

## 🌟 Key Insights

- Distance from Middle East conflict zones correlates with peace
- Island nations and mountainous regions show higher development
- Natural barriers provide protection leading to prosperity
- The “Mesopotamian Paradox” - birthplace of civilization, center of conflict

